If you want to mount the physical disk directly

List all disks
Get-Disk

Unmount it from Windows
Get-Disk 2 | Set-Disk -IsOffline $true

The Windows device path for a physical disk is always: \\.\PhysicalDrive1 or 2 or 3...
Also: --partition 1: Specifies which partition on the disk you want to mount. For example, 
if your disk has 1 exFAT partition, this targets it specifically
Mount it into WSL:
wsl --mount \\.\PhysicalDrive2 --partition 1 --type exfat

Check it:
ls /mnt/wsl

You can then browse it:
ls /mnt/wsl/PHYSICALDRIVE2p1

Unmount it when done:
wsl --unmount \\.\PhysicalDrive2

mount back to Windows
Get-Disk 2 | Set-Disk -IsOffline $false

Get-Partition -DiskNumber 1
Get-Volume
